HEADWORD: Dalbergia
<hw>Dalbergia</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a large genus of tropical trees
having pinnate leaves and paniculate flowers and cultivated commercially
for their dramatically grained and colored timbers.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> genus <gen>Dalbergia</gen>.</syn>⟦br⟧
